onLineSrc.orDesc: Click on the "Download this layer" link to access all digital parcels.

M211TaxPar represents a version of digital municipal parcels for the community of North Attleborough, MA that is considered ‘level 3’ compliant per the specifications outlined in the MassGIS Standard for Digital Parcel Files. Its features can be linked in a GIS or database environment to a set of standardized assessing attributes in the table M211Assess by using the unique identifying values in the LOC_ID field. This data is also intended to be used in conjunction with associated (and optional) features in the ancillary data layers M211OthLeg and M211Misc. As one of the data sets identified by Massachusetts’ Strategic Plan for Spatial Data Infrastructure (http://www.mass.gov/mgis/stratplan.html), this data enters the public domain as a valuable resource for mapping, planning, and analysis at all levels of government as well as the private sector.

dataIdInfo.idAbs: Cadastral data for the Town of North Attleborough, Massachusetts compiled from city tax maps and assessing data. Geometry and attribute data updated on June 2025.

The Town of North Attleborough makes no guarantees express or implied regarding the information contained. The deed serves as the legal definition of all cadastral data.

report.measDesc: This parcel layer contains discrete, non-overlapping polygons for each property. Adjacent polygons with common ownership and a single tax record have been retained in the "OthLeg" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer, and dissolved into single parcels in this TaxPar layer. Some non-adjacent parcels may be represented by multi-part polygons where they share common ownership and a single tax record. Public right of ways exist as polygons, not null space. Linework associated with private ROWs are retained in the "OthLeg" layer. Water polygons also representing parcel boundaries have been retained in this TaxPar layer. Additional water features that are not considered parcel boundaries may have been placed in the "Misc" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer. Easements and other similar non-fee taxable boundaries exist in the 'OthLeg" layer, not the TaxPar layer.

prcStep.stepDesc: Data was processed to meet MassGIS Level III formatting standards including reviewing the city boundary and adding standard fields and definitions. Gaps representing street ROWs were filled in as per the Level III requirements.

Updates were made to the Level III data to reflect the most current version of the town's tax maps as of January 2020 for the town's FY 2021. CAMA data was matched against parcel data to produce a mismatch report which was reconciled with the help of the town. Final QA/QC tool was run.

Updates were made to the Level III data to reflect the most current version of the town's tax maps as of January 2018 for the town's FY 2019. CAMA data was matched against parcel data to produce a mismatch report which was reconciled with the help of the town. Final QA/QC tool was run.

dataSource.srcDesc: Parcel boundaries were originally developed in 2003 from the Town of North Attleborough's 48 80-scale assessors plat maps. These maps provided the linework, dimensions, and Identifiers for the parcel GIS. In 2011, the parcel GIS was updated using city records and updated plat maps.

Updates were made to the Level III data to reflect the most current version of the town's tax maps as of May 2024 for the town's FY 2025. CAMA data was matched against parcel data to produce a mismatch report which was reconciled with the help of the town. Final QA/QC tool was run.

Updates were made to the Level III data to reflect the most current version of the town's tax maps as of May 2025 for the town's FY 2026. CAMA data was matched against parcel data to produce a mismatch report which was reconciled with the help of the town. Final QA/QC tool was run.

overview.dsoverv: Parcel boundaries were originally developed in 2003 from the Town of North Attleborough's 48 80 scale assessors tax maps. Parcels were digitized and referenced to the Town's 40 scale orthophotography. In 2021, the parcel GIS was updated using city records and updated plat maps.

For a full description of the features and attributes contained in this data, please refer to the MassGIS Standard for Digital Parcel Files - v2.0.
